Right > now, every time I run my script I have to close the preexisting windows > and the new windows get assigned ever-increasing numbers. > > I know how to do it for regular R plotting device windows but can not > find a solution for rgl. When you open a new window, it gets a number. (This is shown in the title in Windows. I forget whether other platforms display it, but it's in the return value of open3d()/rgl.open() and rgl.cur().) SOX-101 for Electric, Gas & Water Utilities..An Introduction to Sarbanes-Oxley

APRIL 19-20, 2007 - Chicago, IL
 Click Here To Download A Complete Conference Brochure

 

Overview

This in-depth course is designed for those in a position to be directly impacted by the Sarbanes-Oxley Act, 2002, to include
SAS-70 Reporting requirements, for investor owned and municipal utilities...electric, gas & water. It opens with a detailed review of the current SOX compliance environment and what has guided it to this point, extensive workshops to learn compliance methodologies, and concludes with insight into future direction of the initiative. The seminar uses several approaches to elicit participation from attendees including individual and group exercises for recognizing, creating and documenting internal controls and a case study to simulate experiential learning. All participants are encouraged to ask questions and discuss issues of special interest to them. Extensive and comprehensive course notes are provided to each
attendee.

Register today!

Who Should Attend:

New members of a SOX environment will learn how to be productive immediately and experienced SOX personnel will hone
and focus their skills from the following business categories...

• Managers and Supervisors in Finance, Accounting, Operations and IT personnel
• Internal Audit Personnel ? IT and Finance
• Department Managers impacted by compliance efforts
• Service Providers to the various Utility industries (Electric, Gas & Water), such as Accountants, external IT services,
Customer Service outsourcing providers

What Attendees Will Learn

This intensive one and a half day course will provide participants with a solid understanding of the basic components of internal controls, terms, issues, and methods of documentation necessary to be successful in the audit of compliant internal controls. Attendees will learn the following:

• How to...solve short-term compliance problems by improving your current business processes, rather than adding further overhead. (Get a return on your investment)
• How to...work with your executive team, including your internal and external advisors, to ensure continuity. (No need to replace any trusted advisors)
• How to...improve efficiency by using a risk-based approach to controls and audits (Positions your company for improvement opportunities and Enterprise Risk Management, not just compliance)
• How to...create and maintain internal controls through a better understanding of the components (Who, what, where, when & why)
• How to...identify and document the part IT controls play in the overall control framework

Topics Include:

The History And Future Of Sarbanes-Oxley For Utility Industries
Common SOX Practices in a Utility Enterprise
Focus on IT Controls in a Utility Business
Focus on Internal Controls for Utilities
Risk Assessment Approach to Internal Controls in a Utility
Project Planning Process Improvement - Every Utility Needs It!
Bringing it all Together in Your Utility

About The Instructors:

Mr. Russell "Buddy" Wimberley - Partner, Visage Solutions, LLC
Mr. Wimberley has a diversified operational management background in the utility industry, with hand-on experience in transforming evolving business problems into cost effective technology based solutions concentrating on emerging technologies and business solutions for electric, gas and water utilities. He has broad experience in regulated business unit Asset Management, T&D Planning and budgeting, retail access, customer choice, customer information systems, and commercial/industrial wholesale power customer billing systems.

As a Partner in Visage Solutions, a Sarbanes-Oxley compliance methodology solutions provider he has worked with associates in launching the products and services of the business. For one of the "Big-Four", served as a member of an issue resolution team to perform Information Technology Testing of Internal Controls for Sarbanes Oxley §404 Compliance for a multinational client company with three major business units and twenty-seven data centers. Mr. Wimberley as a member of a SAS-70 Training Team conducted extensive SAS-70 workshops for distributor members of the TVPPA.

Mr. Richard M. Owen, PMP, MBA - Executive Consultant, Visage Solutions, LLC
Mr. Owen has 25 years leadership experience in compliance, ethical business practices and project management in multiple
industries. He continues to provide keynote-speaking engagements on business process improvement, management techniques, project management effectiveness and motivation. Richard is an Adjunct Professor at the University of Houston, Bauer College of Business and Ph.D. Candidate in Leadership Ethics at Our Lady of the Lake University in San Antonio, Texas.

For one of the largest global oil companies, Mr. Owen served as a team lead to perform Walkthrough Documentation, Process Mapping, Design and Testing of Internal Controls of business functions for Sarbanes Oxley §404 Compliance. As a member of a SAS-70 Training Team Mr. Owen has conducted extensive SAS-70 workshops for distributor members of the TVPPA and currently is the Team Lead for the Law, Ethics & Compliance Chapter in the Guide to the Sarbanes-Oxley Body of Knowledge (SOXBoK) as commissioned by the SOX Institute.
